Step 1: sudo apt-get update  //Updates the list of available packages 
Step 2: sudo apt update     //More modern and faster command to fetch package updates.
Step 3: ip a   // Shows all IP addresses assigned to interfaces
Step 4: ip r   //Displays routing table to verify default gateway
Step 5: sudo nano /etc/netplan/01-network-manager-all.yaml (open the file)   //Nano text editor.
Step 6: Modify Network File

6.1: Delete existing YAML content.

6.2: Open FreeCodeCamp static IP guide.

6.3: Copy YAML config before "Step 4".

6.4: Paste it into the Nano file.

6.5: Save (Ctrl+S) and exit (Ctrl+X).
Step 7: sudo netplan apply     // Applies the new network configuration.

Step 8: sudo systemctl restart NetworkManager  //Restarts the network manager to reflect changes.

Step 9: hostname --fqdn  //Shows the fully qualified domain name (expected: ubuntu).
Step 10: Edit /etc/hosts file

10.1: On the 3rd line, add:   <IP Address> apache.cloud.u1 cloud
10.2: Save and exit.

Step 11: sudo hostnamectl set-hostname cloud  //Changes the system hostname to cloud.

Step 12: hostname --fqdn  //Now should return apache.cloud.u1.
